register.description: L2 Memory Protection Fault Address Reg
L2 Memory Protection Fault Status Reg

bitfield.description: Bit 6:0 of faulting requestor. If ID is narrower than 7 bits, the remaining bits return 0. If ID is wider than 7 bits, the additional bits get truncated. FID = 0 if LOCAL = 1.
0 - Normal operation. 1- Access was a "LOCAL" access.

bitfield.description: Interface to initiate a lock/unlock sequence

bitenum.description: Indicates the lock\unlock sequence and resets any state associated with the lock\unlock sequence

bitfield.description: Interface to complete a lock sequence

bitenum.description: Locks the lock provided that the software executed the sequence correctly

bitfield.description: Interface to complete a unlock sequence

bitenum.description: Unlocks the lock provided that the software executed the sequence correctly
